law.text:
The Council on Postsecondary Education in Kentucky shall promote, support, and assist in the program created in KRS 158.798 by:
Identifying college students who have a superior academic aptitude or achievement in math, science, and technology related course work to participate in this program;
Educating higher education institutions as to the availability of this program and encouraging participation by administrators, faculty, and students;
Establishing liaison and assisting in the coordination of any specific program component which involves college-level internships, scholarships, or career development.
